It is free to use, so take advantage of it.

The program also creates people lying down and relaxing, they don't necessarily have to be erotic designs, that will depend more on your checkpoint

items.name: Fire Emblem Three Houses Style | MoosieModel
items.description:
Fire Emblem Three Houses Style V2 is here!

The age relevant tags work a lot better. Younger, Older, Aged up.

This version is much more faithful to the art style of Fire Emblem Three Houses portrait art.

You can replicate the style of character but to replicate the character as they appear in the game, you'll have to mix this FE16 Style LoCon with Fire Emblem LoRAs.

I'm still keeping the weight around 0.7

Have fun!

Please leave a review!

Made using Derrian's SDscripts
Also find me on tensor at tensor.art/u/610807374113953450

--Below is for the v1 LoCON

The New LoCon is much more flexible with a wide variety of checkpoints. Feel free to experiment. The dataset and tagging at the same as the original LoRA. The LoCon remains exceptionally good at generating characters with dark skin.

Oh, I think it's also good for NSFW. I tested it and seems pretty good.

Lastly, you can find some tags from the dataset you can use in your prompts at he bottom.


--Below is for the v2 LoRA

This is a WIP LoRA that replicates the portrait art style of Fire Emblem Three Houses & Fire Emblem Warriors: Three Hopes.

This was trained at 768x768 so it will also best generate images at 768x768 or larger.

I recommend 0.75-0.6 weight for this LoRA. Try different checkpoints, some produce steller results and some produce garbo. Just experiment around, its fun! I use my buddy's Dutch Olympus Model and Dreaming of Olympus which may be released soon if all goes well.

This LoRA can also replicate the different emotions that the character's portraits displayed such as Angry, Blush, Happy, Sad, or Surprised. Just a note. I had better results with Surprised, Open Mouth instead of just Surprised.

This LoRA can replicate the style of the Garrag Mach Monatary outfit as well.

PLEASE leave a review & your comments & opinions because this will not be the final version. I can't even choose between a LoRA or a LoCon.

Also, expect more FE Portrait LoRAs in the future! FE13, FE14, & FE15 are next!

items.name: Arthemy Comics
items.description:
Before to continue with the description of this model - check the Stable Diffusion UI I'm working on right now and streamline your generations!
https://arthemy.ai/

✦ Comics Arthemy - Quick Start ✦

1_____ I highly suggest to use these embeddings:

  • easynegative https://civitai.com/models/7808/easynegative

  • bad-hands-5 https://huggingface.co/yesyeahvh/bad-hands-5/tree/main

  • verybadimagenegative_v1.3 https://civitai.com/models/11772/verybadimagenegativehttps://civitai.com/models/11772/verybadimagenegative

2_____Size: Around 640 x 768

3_____Prompt: Start from the prompt of the pictures I've uploaded and then customize the areas focused on Character, Setting, Emotions, Colors and Aesthetic.

  • Quick Prompt:

    (artwork:1.2),(lineart:1.33),[CHARACTER | SETTING | EMOTIONS],(hyperdefined),(inked-art),[COLORS | AESTHETIC],complex lighting,(flat colors),ultradetailed,(fine-details:1.2),absurdres,(atmosphere)

    easynegative,bad-hands-5, verybadimagenegative_v1.3, (sketch),lowres,(text,words:1.3),watermark,(simple background),glitch,(jpeg-artifact:1.2), desaturated, compressed

4_____Upscale: to get crisp results like the one shown in the pictures use HiResFix and Real-ESRGAN. I suggest to use this step only on the preferred pictures, since it's quite heavy on the performance side.

I hope you like my merge and I can't wait to see what you all are going to create with it!

items.name: Princess Lana - Captain N The Game Master
items.description:
Princess Lana from Captain N The Game Master

Trained on NAI, and IMO works best on it

Generated images were done in NAI, Anything V3 and Anything V4.5 (IMO NAI makes the best), It works decently in neverendingDream, but I didn't upload any images from it.

Keywords: princess lana, pink dress, midriff, skirt, boots

That is the minimum you need to make images if you leave pink dress out the outfit might come out as blue, and if you leave midriff off it tends to make a solid dress.

The skirts color does not tend to come out correctly unless you are at .95-1 strength for the lora, and the boots have from my testing a 40% chance of having the gold band in them

For making this I used 16 screen caps(from a low res grainy videos), a picture from a comic book, and a fan made picture. I took them made a lora that produced acceptable pictures less then 1% of the time. Had SD knock out a few thousand sifted through them and took the best 9 that actually looked good and did some touch ups to make them look perfect, and used them along with most of the original pictures(I removed the comic book one) to generate this lora.

items.name: Abandoned Style
items.description:
About

A style for generating pictures of abandoned things and abandoned places. It adds a touch of rust and decay to everything and everyone. It wasn't intended for generating pictures of people, it will generate pictures of people with rust and decay on their skin (this is known issue - you have been warned). Useful for surreal, horror, post-apocalyptic scenes.

Trained from a single photo of a rusted car in field. This is my first thing I've trained using DreamArtist, constructive feedback is appreciated. I may look at fixing the issues with generating pictures of people in a future version.

Installation

Place in the directory where you keep your embeddings

Usage

use style-abandoned2 in your prompt, experiment with placing it at the beginning, middle or end of your prompt.

items.name: ORCS
items.description:
The orcs are coming! Please rate and leave a like if you enjoyed it.

This LoRA was trained on +700 images of orcs, including anime and 3d, to achieve a higher level of detail, and it can do both SFW and NSFW.

Trained on NAI and seems to work with that lineage of models. The aim is to replace the male characters. I always train it so you can use weight 1.0 and other character and style LoRAs.

How to use:

  • Weight 1.0 with your usual CFG

  • A trigger word is not needed, but you can use the tag orczor for immediate and strong effect. Sometimes you may want to decrease the effect and e.g. use "(orczor:0.x)".

  • Other tags that you can use to modify or amplify the effect: orc, monster, green skin, muscular, size difference, height difference, tusks, glowing eyes, fat, fat man, horror \(theme\), manly, etc. See my example images.

It can also generate detailed SFW orcs (e.g. prompt below: "orczor, face, black eyes, green skin, helmet, armor, beard, bald, horror \(theme\)")

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

Sword Art Online (+ Alicization) Anime style LoRA

Check both version tabs

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️, feel free to buy me a coffee ☕ or just leave a ❤️


This style was requested a lot, but this anime changes a lot between each season, especially from season 1 to Alicization. I decided to make both as two separate models.

Works perfectly on AnyLoRA at weight 1. Increase the accuracy with the trigger sao anime style for the 1st season LoRA, and alicization anime style for the Alicization season LoRA. Also keep in mind your LoRA file name might be different from the ones I used in examples.

(Remember this is a style lora, so while it can probably make similar characters from the game, it might not be super accurate without a character lora. See the examples)

  1. 增加更多细节的同时减少了污染

  2. 更好的背景，更好的背景，衣服，四肢逻辑

  3. 更好的光影效果

  4. 稍稍增加了对比度，画面看起来更加通透

Huge improvements from v1.2 -> v1.3:

  1. More details while reducing unwanted elements.

  2. Improved background details, background, cloth, limbs logics.

  3. Improved lighting and shadows

  4. Slightly increased contrast for better "clarity".

这是我日常使用的融合模型。它有：

  1. 非常好的光影

The Snayperskaya Vintovka Chukavina (meaning "Chukavin Sniper Rifle") is a Gas-operated, Short Stroke Gas Piston with a Rotating Bolt firearm, designed by Andrey Yuryevich Chukavin and unveiled in 2016 as a purpose-built Designated Marksman Rifle, with the intent of taking over the role fulfilled by the now-obsolescent Dragunov SVD.

The firearm is designed with a Lower/Upper Receiver assembly, with a polymer lower and steel upper, minimizing overall weight without sacrificing on rigidity. Other improvements over the Dragunov include: A Full Length Picatinny rail, a new Safety Lever more similar to AR-15's, and a Cold Hammer Forged 410mm (16.1 inch) barrel, but there are variants with longer barrels, as well as a .338 Lapua Magnum variant, that possesses a 560mm (22.2 inch) barrel, designated as the SVCh-8.6.

To further cement the idea that it is a modernization of the Dragunov Weapon System, the SVCh feeds from standard Dragunov magazines when used in the 7.62x54mm Rimmed variant, however, there are two more calibers available - The 7.62x51mm NATO, and the .338 Lapua Magnum.

The standard SVCh weighs in at 4.3 kilograms unloaded (9.48 pounds), while the .338 Lapua Magnum variant weighs 6.3 kilograms (13.89 pounds), making it an exceptionally light gun, although the SVD still beats it in this front, weighing the same 4.3 kilos unloaded, but with its standard PSO-1 scope attached

items.name: Cartunafied
items.description:
• "We are like dwarfs sitting on the shoulders of giants. We see more, and things that are more distant, than they did, not because our sight is superior or because we are taller than they, but because they raise us up, and by their great stature add to ours." - John of Salisbury

  • Credit to CivitAI for providing this space for us, and to the community that seeks ever greater levels of perfection.

____________________

V3-inpainting Notes:

  • Incorrect file version uploaded, I'm fixing that now.

  • Added inpainting capabilities, that's all

  • I recommend trying out the Inpaint Anything extension, they recently added functionality so you can use custom inpainting models

  • I'm working on a potential v4, just need to learn merged block weighting first...

____________________

V3 Notes:

  • v3: Ah, my muse, at last I have found you. Variable skin tones, impressive backgrounds and detailing, much more reliable hands, much cleaner genitals. Even more responsiveness to prompting, and accepts about the same amount of influence from Loras as v2

  • v2: More detailing added, improved hands and keyword responsiveness, but less influenced by Loras, and still kinda prone to naked white women.

  • fp16 (really just v1): Simple, clean style, not a lot of details, can be very influenced by Loras etc. Excellent for basic lined illustrations and can still handle more '2.5D-ish' styling. Not so good with hands, prone to naked white women.

____________________

This model is a merge of 3 4 8 different 'cartoon' style models at varying ratios to provide a much more varied 'western animation' stylizing, while still gaining a lot of responsiveness to prompts and concepts. Use any style of prompts, including danbooru tags, malformed sentence fragments, poetry, go nuts. A wild variety of concepts are recognized, keep it as simple or as complicated as you like. Because that's what I like. And women... I do like the women.

  • There is no VAE baked in. I recommend the standard Stable Diffusion VAEs, Clear VAE, or my own Anime VAE.

  • This model is very capable of soft-core NSFW content, but may struggle with hard-core concepts. Use Loras as needed.

  • All images were generated using only prompting, via an advanced wildcard extension called Umi AI. No additional extensions or post processing techniques were used.

  • If you are concerned about 'apparent age' issues, I highly recommend the following models:
    Squeezer - Experimental
    (A single LoRA with which you use positive strengths to age down, and negative strengths to age up, which impacts details and body type more than overall composition)
    Age Slider
    (A set of Textual Inversions that influence apparent age up and down by 3 levels, including negative embeddings for additional effect. They can affect the composition of your gens in chaotic ways, even with the recommended emphasis values.)

____________________

The following models were used in this merge:

  • (18.75%) UmiAI's Cartoon_Final_v2 unpublished
    see Mythology and Babes by DutchAlex and Macross v2

  • (18.75%) Toonify v2

  • (12.5%) 桥洞底下盖小被，逢人就说对对对

  • (12.5%) Kittenchow

  • (12.5%) Mistoon Amethyst

  • (12.5%) Donated private model and used with permission

  • (6.25%) 23511-1546-幻色石

  • (6.25%) TypeB

____________________

Please run your models through the Model Toolkit extension for A1111. It can fix CLIP corruption and prune models to fp-32 or fp-16.
____________________

DISCLAIMER:
Like all checkpoints since the originals released by Stable Diffusion, this model is responsive to age related keywords. It is also capable of producing NSFW content. What you do with this model is your choice. I suggest not making questionable images by using negative prompting as needed. I am marking this model as intended for mature audiences because of this.
____________________

Also available at Tensor.Art: https://tensor.art/models/612849265988992344
____________________

v2 Notes:

This is a complete re-work adding more top-shelf models. No additional model modifiers like LoRAs were used, this is prompting only. I chose to make grid previews with randomizing prompt structures to showcase the raw capabilities of this model. It is biased to light-skinned women and nudity. It is responsive to all styles of prompting, short, long, keyword lists, sentence fragments, go nuts. You should specify what you want, especially with regards to NSFW conditions.

____________________

- Using UmiAI's wildcard system, you can call for strings of text in both the main prompt and the negative prompt. Items appearing between pairs of asterisks ** will be placed in the negative prompt. The prompts below, followed by the 'quality tags' I used for each style type, are how the example grids were made.

  • <[rngfem]>: "SFW, 1Girl, Adult, ({fat|slutty|cute|muscular} <[rng_intl]>:<[W3.*]>) woman, <[rng_smol]>, (<[rng_hair_multi]>:<[W3.*]>), wearing (<[rng_colors]>:<[W3.*]>) (<[fem_outfit]> outfit:<[W3.*]>), <[rng_gem]> jewelry, <[rng_metal]> accents, glowing {iris|pupils}, <[rng_colors_ext]> eyes, (<[rng_emote]> expression:<[W3.*]>), <[qt_face]>, <[rng_dgrw]>, <[qt_25D]>, <[18+]><[negs_logos]><[negs_body]><[negs_qual]>**naked, nude, **"

  • <[rngxfem]>: "NSFW, 1Girl, Adult, [naked|nude] ({fat|slutty|cute|muscular} <[rng_intl]>:1.2) woman, <[BEWBS]>, <[rng_hair]>, wearing see-through <[rng_colors]> <[fem_outfit]> outfit, <[rng_gem]> jewelry, <[rng_metal]> accents, glowing {iris|pupils}, <[rng_colors]> eyes, <[rng_emote]> expression, <[qt_face]>, <[qt_nsfw]>, <[rng_dg]>, <[18+]>"

  • flat: "flat colors, cel shading, hard shadows, outlines, vector art**realism, photorealistic, hyperrealism, professional photography, uhd, dslr, hdr, ultra high-definition, digital single-lens reflex, high dynamic range, 8k, 3D render**"

  • ani: "depth of field, bokeh, god rays, vivid colors, cinematic hard lighting, smooth shadows"

  • 25d: "subsurface scattering, ray traced, depth of field, bokeh, god rays, vivid colors, cinematic hard lighting, realistic shadows, detailed textures**flat colors, cel shading, hard shadows, vector art, 2D, sketch, background without depth**"

  • photo: "cinematic lighting, depth of field, bokeh, realism, photorealistic, hyperrealism, professional photography, uhd, dslr, hdr**flat colors, cel shading, hard shadows, outlines, vector art, background without depth, 3D render**"

____________________

CFG Scale 20-30 setting is enabled by the following extension: Stable Diffusion Dynamic Thresholding (CFG Scale Fix)

____________________

The following models were used in this merge:

  • (25%) Unpublished "Cartoon2-Final" from the author of Macross V2

  • (25%) Kittenchow

  • (25%) 桥洞底下盖小被，逢人就说对对对

  • (25%) Toonify

____________________

____________________

vFP16 Notes:
This is my first and likely only attempt at merging models. I have no idea what I'm doing and just ran through some tutorials and hit buttons. This model is a merge of 3 4 different 'cartoon' style models to give a blend of more 'western' stylizing while gaining a lot of responsiveness to prompts. Seriously, no need for a prompting guide, it responds to all styles, including anime tags and 'natural language' sentence fragments. This model works well with most LoRAs and negative embeddings. It struggles with hands a bit still and the occasion extra limbs, but otherwise outputs are solid.

Bloodymarrymix 30%

Anything V4.5 30%

MeteoriteDiffusion 10%

And lastly AOM3 30%

Anyways, here is the recommended settings for da model.

Sampler: (THIS IS GONNA BE A SHOCKER) DPM ++ SDE Karras

Hope y'all have fun with this model. Its very good and it can create high quality images very easily, a lot like BMM and MeteoriteDiffusion.

items.name: No Panties? (Hidden Privates)
items.description:
This is a Lora trained on images where a girl is probably or obviously not wearing panties, but pussy is not visible (such as haitenai? tag on pixiv). Most models, especially anime/booru models, can be too eager to go full nsfw when trying to generate suggestive images, and if you add "pussy juice" then it's pretty much impossible to not generate exposed pussy. This Lora will drastically improve consistency when generating those borderline suggestive prompts, and also contains training for various types of ways to display a lack of panties without exposing the crotch. See list of tags below for details.

Main tags:

npmaybe, probably no panties : used on images where the lack of panties is questionable, or at least not too obvious. "probably no panties" will be affected by "no panties", depending on the base model, while "npmaybe" is new so should have an equal, but lesser effect. You can use both, or either, test and see.

npclearly, obviously no panties : used when there's no way girl's wearing underwear. The training didn't really grasp the difference very well, so most of time it won't make any difference which tag you use, but it does sometimes make a difference as shown in the previews.

hidden privates : used on all images in the dataset. Very effective at hiding privates, as you could guess. I would recommend always using it.

hidden crotch or partially visible crotch : one or the other used depending on if the crotch, specifically the area right next to where you would expect the pussy to be, is visible or not. Ex: raising skirt right at the edge so bottom of crotch is barely visible, or a front slit cutting off right next to pussy.

hidden by leg/clothes/hair/tail/border/other : These help hiding the crotch, but the "by" part doesn't seem to do anything. Probably not enough training data for each. "convenient leg" was also added with hidden by leg.

Other new tags :

upthigh : when thigh is visible especially high, above groin. Usually on front view, skirt lift images.

innerthigh : this one's ambiguous and I'm not sure it does much, but it's added on images where you can see the inner thigh right next to the crotch.

sidethigh : when you can see the bare thigh from the side all the way up to the butt. Probably won't do much if the view isn't from the side, use "from side", or "side view" for more moderate effect.

sitbare : when sitting down, usually on floor, with knees up, and you can see the bare bottom of butt. I haven't tested this much, I wouldn't expect a noticeable difference since default generation is like that already.

backcrack : the opposite of groin I guess, lowleg from behind showing butt crack.

underbutt : not a new tag, but putting it here since it's similar to above tags. underboob for butts.

(slightly) lifting one side/both sides of skirt

very lowleg

Relevant existing booru tags :

groin, skirt slit, side slit, front slit, skirt lift, lifted by self, wind lift, skirt tug, microskirt, bottomless, naked shirt/apron/tabard/etc, no bra, convenient censoring,

hair censor (check out hair censor loras, very few images with hair censoring in this one so it probably won't work great on its own),

see-through silhouette (lora for this will also help a lot, otherwise it usually becomes completely see-through, although it does always hide crotch)

Notes

If you'd like, you can check out example (partial) prompts on this wildcard I made to test the lora: https://files.catbox.moe/lb3l8g.txt

The :TT after lora in previews is a preset for the Lora Block Weight extension. It reduces the lora's impact on the background, in particular. To reproduce, add this line in the presets:

TT:1,0.2,0.2,0.2,0.5,0.5,0.5,0.5,1,1,1,1,0.5,0.5,0.5,0.5,0.5

items.name: Simple Blank Backgrounds
items.description:
The goal of this LORA is to generate images with simple blank backgrounds. The LORA was trained on 73 images that have blank backgrounds (most of the images had white backgrounds. Some had grey, black, green, blue, or pink backgrounds).

The LORA does not require any keywords. I tried to train it to use the keyword ssbg but the keyword appears to have no effect in my testing so far (I'm new to creating LORA's so I'm assuming I messed something up when tagging the images). My initial goal was to use the term ssbg for choosing the background color. Terms such as 'red background' or 'green background' can be used to change the color of the desired blank background but they tend to leave white outlines at the edges.

I recommend using a weight between 1 and 2 when using the lora. Weight 1 usually works well, but sometimes increasing the weight may be required.

I have tested this lora on the following models so far: Lyriel, Anythingv4.5, and AnyLora.
